Design decision for phase one - all data stores in ~/iizip and metadata in ~/.iizip
This means the .git dir won't be deleted accidentally by the user (unless they delete enerything in theor home dir, and that's gonna break tons of stuff!)

On first run

	mkdir ~/iizip
	mkdir ~/.iizip

To check out a git repo with .git metadata stored in ~/.iizip do:

	git --git-dir ~/.iizip/ --work-tree ~/iizip init

Sending updates to github:

	git --git-dir ~/.iizip/ --work-tree ./ commit -am 'iizip auto-commit'

Periodic updates:

	git --git-dir ~/.iizip/ --work-tree ./ pull git@github.com:benbalbo/iizip-benbalbo.git
